The paper deals with the problem of model selection in linear regression with regularization, which is a common topic in machine learning and statistics. The use of the Lasso and its asymptotic properties suggest that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of bootstrapping for variable selection, which is a statistical technique, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.ST (Statistics). The use of regularization and model selection is also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper compares its method to other linear regression methods, which is a common practice in the sub-category of stat.ML (Machine Learning).
